snippet: Officials said that 44 people were killed and over 100 were hurt in explosions — some set off by suicide bombers — that targeted public spaces and security checkpoints.
abstract: Explosions targeting public markets and security checkpoints kill 44 people across Iraq and wound over 100.
lead_paragraph: Officials said that 44 people were killed and over 100 were hurt in explosions — some set off by suicide bombers — that targeted public spaces and security checkpoints.

headline.main: Dozens Are Killed in Iraq Bombings
headline.print_headline: Dozens Are Killed In Iraq Bombings
